name: market for cattle for slaughtering, live weight | cattle for slaughtering, live weight | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/20433/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for 'cattle for slaughtering, live weight', in the Global geography. This is a constrained market for consequential system model, for attributional system models, this is a regular market. In the case of consequential system model, details about the marginal consumer can be found in the comment of the conditional exchange (by-product).;This is a market activity delivering cattle to their respective market, i.e.: slaughterhouse. The activity includes transportation.;[This dataset is meant to replace the following datasets:; - market for cattle for slaughtering, live weight, GLO, 2014 - 2014 (54b51015-90ef-4bd3-a69a-a7c28dc4a7e7)];The product 'cattle for slaughtering, live weight' is an animal farmed for meat. Beef cattle are typically farmed for 1-2 years. The product represents the animal alive before transferring and processing in a slaughterhouse.

Activity starts with loading the cattle onto the lorry.

Activity ends with unloading the cattle off the lorry.
